exchangeClusterResourceTable.name: exchangeClusterResourceTable
exchangeClusterResourceTable.description: The ExchangeClusterResource WMI class has properties that return information about a Microsoft Exchange cluster resource.

excrIndex.name: excrIndex
excrIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

excrName.name: excrName
excrName.description: The Name property returns the name of the Microsoft Exchange cluster resource. The Name property is read-only, and is a key property of this class.

excrOwner.name: excrOwner
excrOwner.description: The Owner property for a cluster resource specifies the cluster node of which the resource is a part. The Owner property is read-only.

excrState.name: excrState
excrState.description: The State property specifies the current state of the cluster resource.

excrType.name: excrType
excrType.description: The Type property specifies the resource type.

excrVirtualMachine.name: excrVirtualMachine
excrVirtualMachine.description: The Type property specifies the resource type.

exchangeConnectorStateTable.name: exchangeConnectorStateTable
exchangeConnectorStateTable.description: The ExchangeConnectorState WMI class has properties that return information about a Microsoft Exchange connector.

excsIndex.name: excsIndex
excsIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

excsDN.name: excsDN
excsDN.description: The DN property specifies the Microsoft Active Directory distinguished name (DN) of the Exchange Connector object.

excsGroupDN.name: excsGroupDN
excsGroupDN.description: The GroupDN property specifies the distinguished name (DN) in Active Directory of the routing group.

excsGroupGUID.name: excsGroupGUID
excsGroupGUID.description: The GroupGUID property specifies the globally unique identifier (GUID) of the routing group.

excsGUID.name: excsGUID
excsGUID.description: The GUID property specifies the GUID of the Exchange Connector.

excsIsUp.name: excsIsUp
excsIsUp.description: The IsUp property, when True, specifies that the Exchange Connector is operating normally.

excsName.name: excsName
excsName.description: The Name property specifies the name of the Exchange Connector.

exchangeLinkTable.name: exchangeLinkTable
exchangeLinkTable.description: The ExchangeLink WMI class has properties that return information about message-handling links between mail servers. A link can contain zero or more ExchangeQueue objects, depending on the current message traffic along the link. In the Exchange System Manager, these links are called queues.

exlIndex.name: exlIndex
exlIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exlActionFreeze.name: exlActionFreeze
exlActionFreeze.description: The ActionFreeze property, when True, specifies that the link supports freezing messages in its queues. The ActionFreeze property corresponds to the sixth bit (0x00000020) of the SupportedLinkActions property.

exlActionKick.name: exlActionKick
exlActionKick.description: The ActionKick property, when True, specifies that the link can trigger its queues to retry transmitting waiting messages immediately, instead of waiting for the default protocol timeout before retrying the transmission. The ActionKick property corresponds to the first bit (0x00000001) of the SupportedLinkActions property.

exlActionThaw.name: exlActionThaw
exlActionThaw.description: The ActionThaw property, when True, specifies that the link supports thawing messages in its queues. Thawing a queue is also known as 'unfreezing' that queue. The ActionThaw property corresponds to the seventh bit (0x00000040) of the SupportedLinkActions property.

exlExtendedStateInfo.name: exlExtendedStateInfo
exlExtendedStateInfo.description: The ExtendedStateInfo property specifies the text description of the current link status.

exlGlobalStop.name: exlGlobalStop
exlGlobalStop.description: The GlobalStop property specifies whether the link is currently stopped.

exlIncreasingTime.name: exlIncreasingTime
exlIncreasingTime.description: The IncreasingTime property specifies the amount of time, in milliseconds, that the number of messages waiting to be transferred by the link has been increasing.

exlLinkDN.name: exlLinkDN
exlLinkDN.description: The LinkDN property specifies the Active Directory globally unique identifier (GUID) of the connector object that generated the link.

exlLinkName.name: exlLinkName
exlLinkName.description: The LinkName property specifies the name of the link.

exlNextScheduledConnection.name: exlNextScheduledConnection
exlNextScheduledConnection.description: The NextScheduledConnection property specifies the date and time when a connection will be attempted to transfer waiting messages.

exlNumberOfMessages.name: exlNumberOfMessages
exlNumberOfMessages.description: The NumberOfMessages property specifies the number of messages that are waiting for transmission across the link.

exlOldestMessage.name: exlOldestMessage
exlOldestMessage.description: The OldestMessage property specifies the date and time that the oldest message that is still waiting to be transmitted was received into the link.

exlProtocolName.name: exlProtocolName
exlProtocolName.description: The ProtocolName property specifies the transmission protocol for the link.

exlSizeOfQueue.name: exlSizeOfQueue
exlSizeOfQueue.description: The SizeOfQueue property specifies the total size of the messages in the link, in bytes.

exlStateActive.name: exlStateActive
exlStateActive.description: The StateActive property, when True, specifies that the link is active. The StateActive property corresponds to first bit (0x00000001) of the StateFlags property.

exlStateFlags.name: exlStateFlags
exlStateFlags.description: The StateFlags property specifies the state of the link. The individual bits of this property are available as the link State. and Type. properties of this class.

exlStateFrozen.name: exlStateFrozen
exlStateFrozen.description: The StateFrozen property indicates whether the link is currently frozen. The StateFrozen property corresponds to the sixth bit (0x00000020) of the StateFlags property.

exlStateReady.name: exlStateReady
exlStateReady.description: The StateReady property, when True, specifies that the link is ready to accept new messages. The StateReady property corresponds to the second bit (0x00000002) of the StateFlags property.

exlStateRemote.name: exlStateRemote
exlStateRemote.description: The StateRemote property, when True, specifies that the destination for messages in this link is on a remote server, instead of the messages being delivered to a local store. The StateRemote property corresponds to the fifth bit (0x00000010) of the StateFlags property.

exlStateRetry.name: exlStateRetry
exlStateRetry.description: The StateRetry property, when True, specifies that the link is retrying a transmission that was unsuccessful. The StateRetry property corresponds to the third bit (0x00000004) of the StateFlags property.

exlStateScheduled.name: exlStateScheduled
exlStateScheduled.description: The StateScheduled property, when True, specifies that the link is scheduled for periodic activation, as compared with asynchronous, on-demand activation. The StateScheduled property corresponds to the fourth bit (0x00000008) of the StateFlags property.

exlSupportedLinkActions.name: exlSupportedLinkActions
exlSupportedLinkActions.description: The SupportedLinkActions property specifies the actions supported by the link. The individual bits of this property are available as the Action. properties in this class.

exlTypeCurrentlyUnreachable.name: exlTypeCurrentlyUnreachable
exlTypeCurrentlyUnreachable.description: The TypeCurrentlyUnreachable property, when True, specifies that the link holds messages for destinations that currently cannot be reached. The TypeCurrentlyUnreachable property corresponds to the thirteenth bit (0x00001000) of the StateFlags property.

exlTypeDeferredDelivery.name: exlTypeDeferredDelivery
exlTypeDeferredDelivery.description: The TypeDeferredDelivery property, when True, specifies that the link holds mail that is awaiting a trigger to start transmission. The TypeDeferredDelivery property corresponds to the fourteenth bit (0x00002000) of the StateFlags property.

exlTypeInternal.name: exlTypeInternal
exlTypeInternal.description: The TypeInternal property indicates that the link is used for internal message processing. The TypeInternal property corresponds to the fifteenth bit (0x00004000) of the StateFlags property.

exlTypeLocalDelivery.name: exlTypeLocalDelivery
exlTypeLocalDelivery.description: The TypeLocalDelivery property, when True, specifies that the link handles local mail delivery. The TypeLocalDelivery property corresponds to the tenth bit (0x00000200) of the StateFlags property.

exlTypePendingCategorization.name: exlTypePendingCategorization
exlTypePendingCategorization.description: The TypePendingCategorization property, when True, specifies that the link is resolving addresses against entries in Active Directory. The TypePendingCategorization property corresponds to the twelfth bit (0x00000800) of the StateFlags property.

exlTypePendingRouting.name: exlTypePendingRouting
exlTypePendingRouting.description: The TypePendingRouting property, when True, specifies that the link is determining the routing of the next message that is waiting to be transmitted. The TypePendingRouting property corresponds to the eleventh bit (0x00000400) of the StateFlags property.

exlTypePendingSubmission.name: exlTypePendingSubmission
exlTypePendingSubmission.description: The TypePendingSubmission property, when True, specifies that the link handles messages that have not yet been submitted to the routing engine. The TypePendingSubmission property corresponds to the sixteenth bit (0x00008000) of the StateFlags property.

exlTypeRemoteDelivery.name: exlTypeRemoteDelivery
exlTypeRemoteDelivery.description: The TypeRemoteDelivery property, when True, specifies that the link is currently handling a remote message delivery. The TypeRemoteDelivery property corresponds to the ninth bit (0x00000100) of the StateFlags property.

exlVersion.name: exlVersion
exlVersion.description: The Version property specifies the version number of the underlying link control software.

exlVirtualMachine.name: exlVirtualMachine
exlVirtualMachine.description: The VirtualMachine property specifies the name of the virtual machine that is the source of the link.

exlVirtualServerName.name: exlVirtualServerName
exlVirtualServerName.description: The value of the VirtualServerName property is the integer number of the virtual machine that is the source of the link. This number is the Microsoft Active Directorycommon name (CN) for the virtual server object.

exchangeQueueTable.name: exchangeQueueTable
exchangeQueueTable.description: The ExchangeQueue WMI class has properties that return information about the dynamic queues created to transfer individual messages between mail servers. An ExchangeQueue is part of an ExchangeLink. ExchangeQueue objects are not the same as the queues listed in the Exchange System Manager.

exqIndex.name: exqIndex
exqIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exqCanEnumAll.name: exqCanEnumAll
exqCanEnumAll.description: The CanEnumAll property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate all of the messages that it has waiting for transmission. The CanEnumAll property corresponds to the thirty-first bit (0x40000000) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumFailed.name: exqCanEnumFailed
exqCanEnumFailed.description: The CanEnumFailed property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the messages that it has waiting for transmission that it was unable to transfer. The CanEnumFailed property corresponds to the ninth bit (0x00000100) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumFirstNMessages.name: exqCanEnumFirstNMessages
exqCanEnumFirstNMessages.description: The CanEnumFirstNMessages property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the first N messages that it has waiting for transmission. The CanEnumFirstNMessages property corresponds to the first bit (0x00000001) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumFrozen.name: exqCanEnumFrozen
exqCanEnumFrozen.description: The CanEnumFrozen property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate messages that it has waiting for transmission that have been frozen. The CanEnumFrozen property corresponds to the sixth bit (0x00000020) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumInvertSense.name: exqCanEnumInvertSense
exqCanEnumInvertSense.description: The CanEnumInvertSense property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate messages that it has waiting for transmission that do not match the criteria requested. For example, requesting the oldest messages while inverting the request sense would return the newest messages. The CanEnumInvertSense property corresponds to the thirty-second bit (0x80000000) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumLargerThan.name: exqCanEnumLargerThan
exqCanEnumLargerThan.description: The CanEnumLargerThan property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the messages that it has waiting for transmission that are larger than a specified value. The CanEnumLargerThan property corresponds to the fourth bit (0x00000008) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumNLargestMessages.name: exqCanEnumNLargestMessages
exqCanEnumNLargestMessages.description: The CanEnumNLargestMessages property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the specified number of the largest messages that it has waiting for transmission. The CanEnumNLargestMessages property corresponds to the seventh bit (0x00000040) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumNOldestMessages.name: exqCanEnumNOldestMessages
exqCanEnumNOldestMessages.description: The CanEnumNOldestMessages property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the specified number of the oldest messages that it has waiting for transmission. The CanEnumNOldestMessages property corresponds to the eighth bit (0x00000080) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumOlderThan.name: exqCanEnumOlderThan
exqCanEnumOlderThan.description: The CanEnumOlderThan property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the messages that it has waiting for transmission that arrived before a specified date and time. The CanEnumOlderThan property corresponds to the fifth bit (0x00000010) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumRecipient.name: exqCanEnumRecipient
exqCanEnumRecipient.description: The CanEnumRecipient property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the recipients of messages that it has waiting for transmission. The CanEnumRecipient property corresponds to the fourth bit (0x00000004) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqCanEnumSender.name: exqCanEnumSender
exqCanEnumSender.description: The CanEnumSender property, when True, specifies that the queue can enumerate the senders of messages that it has waiting for transmission. The CanEnumSender property corresponds to the second bit (0x00000002) of the MsgEnumFlagsSupported property.

exqGlobalStop.name: exqGlobalStop
exqGlobalStop.description: The GlobalStop property specifies whether the queue is currently stopped.

exqIncreasingTime.name: exqIncreasingTime
exqIncreasingTime.description: The IncreasingTime property specifies the amount of time, in milliseconds, that the number of messages waiting to be transferred by the queue has been increasing.

exqLinkName.name: exqLinkName
exqLinkName.description: The LinkName property specifies the name of the link in which this queue is contained.

exqMsgEnumFlagsSupported.name: exqMsgEnumFlagsSupported
exqMsgEnumFlagsSupported.description: The MsgEnumFlagsSupported property specifies a bit-mapped set of flags that indicate what types of objects can be enumerated. The individual bits of this property are available as the queue CanEnum. properties in this class.

exqNumberOfMessages.name: exqNumberOfMessages
exqNumberOfMessages.description: The NumberOfMessages property specifies the number of messages that are waiting for transmission by the queue.

exqProtocolName.name: exqProtocolName
exqProtocolName.description: The ProtocolName property specifies the transmission protocol for the queue.

exqQueueName.name: exqQueueName
exqQueueName.description: The QueueName property specifies the name of the queue.

exqSizeOfQueue.name: exqSizeOfQueue
exqSizeOfQueue.description: The SizeOfQueue property specifies the total size of all messages in the queue, in bytes.

exqVersion.name: exqVersion
exqVersion.description: The Version property specifies the version number of the Microsoft Exchange software.

exqVirtualMachine.name: exqVirtualMachine
exqVirtualMachine.description: The VirtualMachine property specifies the name of the virtual machine that is the source of the link.

exqVirtualServerName.name: exqVirtualServerName
exqVirtualServerName.description: The value of the VirtualServerName property is the integer number of the virtual machine that is the source of the queue. This number is the Microsoft Active Directory common name (CN) for the virtual server object.

exchangeServerStateTable.name: exchangeServerStateTable
exchangeServerStateTable.description: The ExchangeServerState WMI class has properties that return information about the computer running Microsoft Exchange 2000 Server.

exssIndex.name: exssIndex
exssIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exssClusterState.name: exssClusterState
exssClusterState.description: When the ExchangeServerState instance represents a clustered Exchange server, the ClusterState property specifies the state of the clustered resources on that server.

exssClusterStateString.name: exssClusterStateString
exssClusterStateString.description: When the ExchangeServerState instance represents a clustered Exchange server, the ClusterStateString property specifies the state of the cluster resources on that server.

exssCPUState.name: exssCPUState
exssCPUState.description: The CPUState property specifies the current state of the CPU on the Exchange server. This is the same state information shown on the Monitoring and Status Properties page of the Exchange System Manager.

exssCPUStateString.name: exssCPUStateString
exssCPUStateString.description: The CPUStateString property specifies the current state of the CPU on the Exchange server.

exssDisksState.name: exssDisksState
exssDisksState.description: The DisksState property specifies the current state of the disk storage on the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssDisksStateString.name: exssDisksStateString
exssDisksStateString.description: The DisksStateString property specifies the current state of the disk storage on the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssDN.name: exssDN
exssDN.description: The DN property specifies the Microsoft Active Directory distinguished name (DN) of the Exchange server object.

exssGroupDN.name: exssGroupDN
exssGroupDN.description: The GroupDN property specifies the DN of the Exchange 2000 Server routing group in Active Directory.

exssGroupGUID.name: exssGroupGUID
exssGroupGUID.description: The GroupGUID property specifies the globally unique identifier (GUID) of the Exchange 2000 Server routing group in Active Directory.

exssGUID.name: exssGUID
exssGUID.description: The GUID property specifies the GUID of the Exchange 2000 Server server object in Active Directory.

exssMemoryState.name: exssMemoryState
exssMemoryState.description: The MemoryState property specifies the current state of the memory on the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssMemoryStateString.name: exssMemoryStateString
exssMemoryStateString.description: The MemoryStateString property specifies the current state of the memory on the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssName.name: exssName
exssName.description: The Name property specifies the name of the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssQueuesState.name: exssQueuesState
exssQueuesState.description: The QueuesState property specifies the current state of the queues on the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssQueuesStateString.name: exssQueuesStateString
exssQueuesStateString.description: The QueuesStateString property specifies the current state of the queues on the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssServerMaintenance.name: exssServerMaintenance
exssServerMaintenance.description: The ServerMaintenance property, when True, specifies that the notifications set up in the Exchange 2000 Server System Manager Monitoring and Status page have been disabled.

exssServerState.name: exssServerState
exssServerState.description: The ServerState property specifies the current state of the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssServerStateString.name: exssServerStateString
exssServerStateString.description: The ServerStateString property specifies the current state of the computer running Exchange 2000 Server.

exssServicesState.name: exssServicesState
exssServicesState.description: The ServicesState property specifies the current state of the monitoring services running on the Exchange 2000 Server computer.

exssServicesStateString.name: exssServicesStateString
exssServicesStateString.description: The ServicesStateString property specifies the current state of the monitoring services running on the Exchange 2000 Server computer.

exssUnreachable.name: exssUnreachable
exssUnreachable.description: The Unreachable property, when True, specifies that the Exchange 2000 Server computer is currently unreachable.

exssVersion.name: exssVersion
exssVersion.description: The Version property indicates the version of the Exchange server.

exchangeDSAccessDCTable.name: exchangeDSAccessDCTable
exchangeDSAccessDCTable.description: The properties of the Exchange_DSAccessDC class provide information about Microsoft Active Directory and Microsoft Exchange Server 5.5 domain controllers that are accessible to the Exchange 2000 Server DSAccess service.

exdsIndex.name: exdsIndex
exdsIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exdsConfigurationType.name: exdsConfigurationType
exdsConfigurationType.description: The ConfigurationType property indicates whether the instance describes a domain controller that was detected automatically, or one that was specified manually.

exdsIsFast.name: exdsIsFast
exdsIsFast.description: The IsFast property indicates, when True, that the domain controller response time has been less than two seconds.

exdsIsInSync.name: exdsIsInSync
exdsIsInSync.description: The IsInSync property indicates whether the domain controller is synchronized with the Global Catalog server and with the Configuration domain controller.

exdsIsUp.name: exdsIsUp
exdsIsUp.description: The IsUp property indicates whether the domain controller was available the last time Exchange attempted to access it.

exdsLDAPPort.name: exdsLDAPPort
exdsLDAPPort.description: The LDAPPort property specifies the TCP/IP port on which the domain controller listens for LDAP requests.

exdsName.name: exdsName
exdsName.description: The Name property specifies the computer name of the domain controller.

exdsType.name: exdsType
exdsType.description: The Type property specifies the role that the domain controller plays in the Exchange system.

exchangeFolderTreeTable.name: exchangeFolderTreeTable
exchangeFolderTreeTable.description: Instances of the Exchange_FolderTree WMI class provide information about public and private folder trees on Microsoft Exchange servers.

exftIndex.name: exftIndex
exftIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exftAdministrativeGroup.name: exftAdministrativeGroup
exftAdministrativeGroup.description: The AdministrativeGroup property indicates the name of the administrative group that the top-level hierarchy (TLH) resides under in Active Directory.

exftAdministrativeNote.name: exftAdministrativeNote
exftAdministrativeNote.description: The AdministrativeNote property indicates the administrative note attached to the Microsoft Active Directory object representing the tree.

exftAssociatedPublicStores.name: exftAssociatedPublicStores
exftAssociatedPublicStores.description: The AssociatedPublicStores property indicates the list of MDBs associated with the top-level hierarchy (TLH).

exftCreationTime.name: exftCreationTime
exftCreationTime.description: The CreationTime property indicates when the tree was created.

exftGUID.name: exftGUID
exftGUID.description: The GUID property indicates the globally unique identifier (GUID) attribute of the top-level hierarchy (TLH) object in Active Directory.

exftHasLocalPublicStore.name: exftHasLocalPublicStore
exftHasLocalPublicStore.description: The HasLocalPublicStore property indicates whether the computer contains the Exchange store associated with the folder tree.

exftLastModificationTime.name: exftLastModificationTime
exftLastModificationTime.description: The LastModificationTime property indicates when the tree was last modified.

exftMapiFolderTree.name: exftMapiFolderTree
exftMapiFolderTree.description: The MapiFolderTree property indicates whether this is the MAPI top-level hierarchy (TLH).

exftName.name: exftName
exftName.description: The Name property indicates the name of the top-level hierarchy (TLH).

exftRootFolderURL.name: exftRootFolderURL
exftRootFolderURL.description: The RootFolderURL property indicates the URL to the root of the tree referenced through the Exchange administration IIS virtual directory.

exl2LinkName.name: exl2LinkName
exl2LinkName.description: The LinkName property indicates the name of the link.

exl2TypePendingRouting.name: exl2TypePendingRouting
exl2TypePendingRouting.description: The TypePendingRouting property, when TRUE, specifies that the link is determining the routing of the next message that is waiting to be transmitted. The TypePendingRouting property corresponds to the eleventh bit (0x00000400) of the StateFlags property.

exl2TypePendingSubmission.name: exl2TypePendingSubmission
exl2TypePendingSubmission.description: The TypePendingSubmission property, when TRUE, specifies that the link handles messages that have not yet been submitted to the routing engine. The TypePendingSubmission property corresponds to the sixteenth bit (0x00008000) of the StateFlags property.

exl2TypeRemoteDelivery.name: exl2TypeRemoteDelivery
exl2TypeRemoteDelivery.description: The TypeRemoteDelivery property, when TRUE, specifies that the link is currently handling a remote message delivery. The TypeRemoteDelivery property corresponds to the ninth bit (0x00000100) of the StateFlags property.

exl2Version.name: exl2Version
exl2Version.description: The Version property specifies the version number of the underlying link control software.

exl2VirtualMachine.name: exl2VirtualMachine
exl2VirtualMachine.description: The VirtualMachine property indicates the name of the virtual machine that is the source of the link.

exl2VirtualServerName.name: exl2VirtualServerName
exl2VirtualServerName.description: The value of the VirtualServerName property is the integer number of the virtual machine that is the source of the link. This number is the Microsoft Active Directory common name (CN) for the virtual server object.

exchangeLogonTable.name: exchangeLogonTable
exchangeLogonTable.description: Instances of Exchange_Logon represent the users currently logged on to Microsoft Exchange.

exloIndex.name: exloIndex
exloIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exloAdapterSpeed.name: exloAdapterSpeed
exloAdapterSpeed.description: The AdapterSpeed property indicates the speed of the client network interface card, in kilobits/second

exloClientIP.name: exloClientIP
exloClientIP.description: The ClientIP property indicates the IP address of the client computer.

exloClientMode.name: exloClientMode
exloClientMode.description: The ClientMode property indicates whether the client is using local data caching.

exloClientName.name: exloClientName
exloClientName.description: The ClientName property indicates the client computer name.

exloClientVersion.name: exloClientVersion
exloClientVersion.description: The ClientVersion property indicates the version of the client used to log on.

exloCodePageID.name: exloCodePageID
exloCodePageID.description: The CodePageID property indicates the code page of the client.

exloFolderOperationRate.name: exloFolderOperationRate
exloFolderOperationRate.description: The FolderOperationRate property indicates the folder operation rate (per second) performed by the store on behalf of the client.

exloHostAddress.name: exloHostAddress
exloHostAddress.description: The HostAddress property indicates the client-specific identification information.

exloLastOperationTime.name: exloLastOperationTime
exloLastOperationTime.description: The LastOperationTime property indicates the time when the last operation was performed.

exloLatency.name: exloLatency
exloLatency.description: The Latency property indicates the server response latency time reported by the client, in milliseconds.

exloLocaleID.name: exloLocaleID
exloLocaleID.description: The LocaleID property indicates the Windows locale of the client.

exloLoggedOnUserAccount.name: exloLoggedOnUserAccount
exloLoggedOnUserAccount.description: The LoggedOnUserAccount property indicates the name of the user account that logged on in the format DOMAIN\SAMAccountName.

exloLoggedOnUsersMailboxLegacyDN.name: exloLoggedOnUsersMailboxLegacyDN
exloLoggedOnUsersMailboxLegacyDN.description: The LoggedOnUsersMailboxLegacyDN property indicates the legacyDN of the user who is currently logged on.

exloLogonTime.name: exloLogonTime
exloLogonTime.description: The LogonTime property indicates the time that the user logged on.

exloMacAddress.name: exloMacAddress
exloMacAddress.description: The MacAddress property indicates the network interface card Media Access Connector address of the client computer.

exloMailboxDisplayName.name: exloMailboxDisplayName
exloMailboxDisplayName.description: The MailboxDisplayName property indicates the name of the mailbox.

exloMailboxLegacyDN.name: exloMailboxLegacyDN
exloMailboxLegacyDN.description: The MailboxLegacyDN property indicates the legacyDN of the mailbox.

exloMessagingOperationRate.name: exloMessagingOperationRate
exloMessagingOperationRate.description: The MessagingOperationRate property indicates the rate of send/receive operations performed per second by the store on behalf of the client.

exloOpenAttachmentCount.name: exloOpenAttachmentCount
exloOpenAttachmentCount.description: The OpenAttachmentCount property indicates the number of attachments currently opened by the client.

exloOpenFolderCount.name: exloOpenFolderCount
exloOpenFolderCount.description: The OpenFolderCount property indicates the number of folders currently opened by the client.

exloOpenMessageCount.name: exloOpenMessageCount
exloOpenMessageCount.description: The OpenMessageCount property indicates the number of messages currently opened by the client.

exloOtherOperationRate.name: exloOtherOperationRate
exloOtherOperationRate.description: The OtherOperationRate property indicates the rate of operations performed on the store, in response to client requests that are not within the other categories of operation-request properties.

exloProgressOperationRate.name: exloProgressOperationRate
exloProgressOperationRate.description: The ProgressOperationRate property indicates the rate of progress operations performed per second by the store on behalf of the client.

exloRowID.name: exloRowID
exloRowID.description: The RowID property indicates that a random identifier is generated per query to ensure uniqueness.

exloRPCSucceeded.name: exloRPCSucceeded
exloRPCSucceeded.description: The RPCSucceeded property indicates the number of successful RPC requests made by the client.

exloServerName.name: exloServerName
exloServerName.description: The ServerName property indicates the name of the server where the mailbox resides.

exloStorageGroupName.name: exloStorageGroupName
exloStorageGroupName.description: The StorageGroupName property indicates the name of the storage group that contains the mailbox.

exloStoreName.name: exloStoreName
exloStoreName.description: The StoreName property indicates the name of the MDB that contains the mailbox.

exloStoreType.name: exloStoreType
exloStoreType.description: The StoreType property indicates whether the store contains mailboxes or public folders.

exloStreamOperationRate.name: exloStreamOperationRate
exloStreamOperationRate.description: The StreamOperationRate property indicates the rate of stream operations performed per second by the store on behalf of the client.

exloTableOperationRate.name: exloTableOperationRate
exloTableOperationRate.description: The TableOperationRate property indicates the rate of table operations performed per second by the store on behalf of the client.

exloTotalOperationRate.name: exloTotalOperationRate
exloTotalOperationRate.description: The TotalOperationRate property indicates the rate of all operations performed per second by the store on behalf of the client.

exloTransferOperationRate.name: exloTransferOperationRate
exloTransferOperationRate.description: The TransferOperationRate property indicates the rate of transfer operations performed per second by the store on behalf of the client.

exchangeMailboxTable.name: exchangeMailboxTable
exchangeMailboxTable.description: The Exchange_Mailbox WMI class has properties that return information about Microsoft Exchange mailboxes.

exmIndex.name: exmIndex
exmIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exmAssocContentCount.name: exmAssocContentCount
exmAssocContentCount.description: The AssocContentCount property indicates the total number of messages associated with the mailbox folders.

exmDateDiscoveredAbsentInDS.name: exmDateDiscoveredAbsentInDS
exmDateDiscoveredAbsentInDS.description: The DateDiscoveredAbsentInDS property indicates when the store detected that the mailbox no longer had a corresponding user entry in Microsoft Active Directory.

exmDeletedMessageSizeExtended.name: exmDeletedMessageSizeExtended
exmDeletedMessageSizeExtended.description: The DeletedMessageSizeExtended property indicates the cumulative size of all deleted messages that are still being retained according to retention policy settings.

exmLastLoggedOnUserAccount.name: exmLastLoggedOnUserAccount
exmLastLoggedOnUserAccount.description: The LastLoggedOnUserAccount property indicates the account name last used to log on to the mailbox.

exmLastLogoffTime.name: exmLastLogoffTime
exmLastLogoffTime.description: The LastLogoffTime property indicates the time that the last user logged off.

exmLastLogonTime.name: exmLastLogonTime
exmLastLogonTime.description: The LastLogonTime property indicates the time that the last user logged on.

exmLegacyDN.name: exmLegacyDN
exmLegacyDN.description: The LegacyDN property indicates the legacyDN of the mailbox and matches the legacyDN attribute of the user object in Microsoft Active Directory.

exmMailboxDisplayName.name: exmMailboxDisplayName
exmMailboxDisplayName.description: The MailboxDisplayName property indicates the display name of the mailbox and matches the displayName attribute in Microsoft Active Directory.

exmMailboxGUID.name: exmMailboxGUID
exmMailboxGUID.description: The MailboxGUID property indicates the globally unique identifier (GUID) that links the mailbox to a user in Microsoft Active Directory.

exmServerName.name: exmServerName
exmServerName.description: The ServerName property indicates the name of the server where the mailbox resides.

exmSize.name: exmSize
exmSize.description: The Size property indicates the cumulative size of all of the messages in the mailbox, in bytes.

exmStorageGroupName.name: exmStorageGroupName
exmStorageGroupName.description: The StorageGroupName property indicates the name of the storage group that contains the mailbox.

exmStorageLimitInfo.name: exmStorageLimitInfo
exmStorageLimitInfo.description: The StorageLimitInfo property contains the storage limit settings on the mailbox.

exmStoreName.name: exmStoreName
exmStoreName.description: The StoreName property indicates the name of the MDB that contains the mailbox.

exmTotalItems.name: exmTotalItems
exmTotalItems.description: The TotalItems property indicates the total number of messages in the mailbox.

exchangeMessageTrackingTable.name: exchangeMessageTrackingTable
exchangeMessageTrackingTable.description: Instances of the Exchange_MessageTrackingEntry class provide information about events that have occurred to the message during the time it was under the control of the computer running Microsoft Exchange 2000 Server.

exmtIndex.name: exmtIndex
exmtIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exmtAttemptedPartnerServer.name: exmtAttemptedPartnerServer
exmtAttemptedPartnerServer.description: The AttemptedPartnerServer property indicates the server to which Exchange tried to send a message, but was unable to complete the transfer.

exmtClientIP.name: exmtClientIP
exmtClientIP.description: The ClientIP property indicates the TCP/IP address of the messaging client that originally submitted the message.

exmtClientName.name: exmtClientName
exmtClientName.description: The ClientName property indicates the name of the messaging client application that submitted the message.

exmtCost.name: exmtCost
exmtCost.description: The Cost property indicates the relative effort required to transfer the message. There are no specific units used in this property. Higher values indicate that slower network connections must be used, or that a greater number of transfers is required to transfer the message.

exmtDeliveryTime.name: exmtDeliveryTime
exmtDeliveryTime.description: The DeliveryTime property indicates the amount of time, in seconds, required to deliver the message.

exmtEncrypted.name: exmtEncrypted
exmtEncrypted.description: The Encrypted property indicates, when True, that the message is encrypted.

exmtEntryType.name: exmtEntryType
exmtEntryType.description: The EntryType property indicates what occurred to cause the message tracking log entry to be created.

exmtExpansionDL.name: exmtExpansionDL
exmtExpansionDL.description: The ExpansionDL property indicates the name of the Exchange distribution list that was expanded. After the distribution list is expanded, the message recipient list includes the names of the individual members of that distribution list.

exmtKeyID.name: exmtKeyID
exmtKeyID.description: The KeyID property uniquely identifies the message log entry.

exmtLinkedMessageID.name: exmtLinkedMessageID
exmtLinkedMessageID.description: The LinkedMessageID property is the string identifier assigned to the message when it is received by the PartnerServer property. This property sometimes has the same value as the MessageID Property.

exmtMessageID.name: exmtMessageID
exmtMessageID.description: The MessageID property indicates the identifier string for the message. The identifier may be assigned by the messaging client application or by the Exchange server.

exmtOriginationTime.name: exmtOriginationTime
exmtOriginationTime.description: The OriginationTime property indicates the date and time, in UTC, when the message was received by Exchange.

exmtPartnerServer.name: exmtPartnerServer
exmtPartnerServer.description: The PartnerServer property indicates the server to which Exchange transferred the message.

exmtPriority.name: exmtPriority
exmtPriority.description: The Priority property specifies the importance of the message, as displayed by the messaging client application.

exmtRecipientAddress.name: exmtRecipientAddress
exmtRecipientAddress.description: The RecipientAddress property returns an array. Each array element contains the e-mail address of one of the message recipients.

exmtRecipientCount.name: exmtRecipientCount
exmtRecipientCount.description: The RecipientCount property indicates how many recipients are in the recipients list for the message.

exmtRecipientStatus.name: exmtRecipientStatus
exmtRecipientStatus.description: Each element of the RecipientStatus array indicates the message type sent to the recipient specified in the corresponding element of the RecipientAddress array.

exmtSenderAddress.name: exmtSenderAddress
exmtSenderAddress.description: The SenderAddress property specifies the e-mail address of the message sender.

exmtServerIP.name: exmtServerIP
exmtServerIP.description: The ServerIP property indicates the TCP/IP protocol address of the Exchange server.

exmtServerName.name: exmtServerName
exmtServerName.description: The ServerName property indicates the name of the virtual server instance that created the message tracking log entry.

exmtSize.name: exmtSize
exmtSize.description: The Size property indicates the message size, including attachments, in bytes.

exmtSubject.name: exmtSubject
exmtSubject.description: The Subject property indicates the subject of the message, as found in the Subject: message header.

exmtSubjectID.name: exmtSubjectID
exmtSubjectID.description: The SubjectID property specifies an identifier created by the messaging client application.

exmtTimeLogged.name: exmtTimeLogged
exmtTimeLogged.description: The TimeLogged property indicates the date and time, in UTC, when the message tracking log entry was created.

exmtVersion.name: exmtVersion
exmtVersion.description: The Version property indicates the version of the service that created the message tracking log entry.

exchangePublicFolderTable.name: exchangePublicFolderTable
exchangePublicFolderTable.description: The Exchange_PublicFolder WMI class provides properties and methods for working with Microsoft Exchange public folders.

expfIndex.name: expfIndex
expfIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

expfAddressBookName.name: expfAddressBookName
expfAddressBookName.description: The AddressBookName property specifies the address book name of the folder.

expfAdministrativeNote.name: expfAdministrativeNote
expfAdministrativeNote.description: The AdministrativeNote property specifies the administrative note associated with the folder.

expfAdminSecurityDescriptor.name: expfAdminSecurityDescriptor
expfAdminSecurityDescriptor.description: The AdminSecurityDescriptor property specifies the security descriptor that is used when a user logs on to the store with administrative privileges.

expfADProxyPath.name: expfADProxyPath
expfADProxyPath.description: The ADProxyPath property indicates the globally unique identifier (GUID) of the Active Directory mail proxy for the folder.

expfAssociatedMessageCount.name: expfAssociatedMessageCount
expfAssociatedMessageCount.description: The AssociatedMessageCount property is a MAPI property that contains the total number of associated messages in the public folder.

expfAttachmentCount.name: expfAttachmentCount
expfAttachmentCount.description: The AttachmentCount property indicates the total number of attachments on all normal messages in a folder.

expfCategorizationCount.name: expfCategorizationCount
expfCategorizationCount.description: The CategorizationCount property indicates the total number of categorizations on the public folder.

expfComment.name: expfComment
expfComment.description: The Comment property specifies the folder comment.

expfContactCount.name: expfContactCount
expfContactCount.description: The ContactCount property indicates the number of contacts in a public folder.

expfContainsRules.name: expfContainsRules
expfContainsRules.description: The ContainsRules property indicates whether the public folder contains rules.

expfCreationTime.name: expfCreationTime
expfCreationTime.description: The CreationTime property indicates when the folder was created.

expfDeletedItemLifetime.name: expfDeletedItemLifetime
expfDeletedItemLifetime.description: The DeletedItemLifetime property specifies how long, in days, that deleted messages can be recovered.

expfFolderTree.name: expfFolderTree
expfFolderTree.description: The FolderTree property indicates the WMI path to the top-level hierarchy object to which the folder belongs.

expfFriendlyUrl.name: expfFriendlyUrl
expfFriendlyUrl.description: The FriendlyUrl property indicates the path-based URL to the folder.

expfHasChildren.name: expfHasChildren
expfHasChildren.description: The HasChildren property indicates whether the folder has subfolders.

expfHasLocalReplica.name: expfHasLocalReplica
expfHasLocalReplica.description: The HasLocalReplica property indicates whether the folder has a local replica.

expfIsMailEnabled.name: expfIsMailEnabled
expfIsMailEnabled.description: The IsMailEnabled property specifies whether the folder is mail-enabled.

expfIsNormalFolder.name: expfIsNormalFolder
expfIsNormalFolder.description: The IsNormalFolder property indicates whether the public folder is a normal folder.

expfIsPerUserReadDisabled.name: expfIsPerUserReadDisabled
expfIsPerUserReadDisabled.description: The IsPerUserReadDisabled property specifies whether the folder tracks per-user read information for messages.

expfIsSearchFolder.name: expfIsSearchFolder
expfIsSearchFolder.description: The IsSearchFolder property indicates whether the public folder is a search folder.

expfIsSecureInSite.name: expfIsSecureInSite
expfIsSecureInSite.description: The IsSecureInSite property specifies whether administrative access is limited to the home site of the folder.

expfLastAccessTime.name: expfLastAccessTime
expfLastAccessTime.description: The LastAccessTime property indicates the last date that the replica of a public folder was accessed.

expfLastModificationTime.name: expfLastModificationTime
expfLastModificationTime.description: The LastModificationTime property indicates when the folder was last modified.

expfMaximumItemSize.name: expfMaximumItemSize
expfMaximumItemSize.description: The MaximumItemSize property specifies the maximum size, in kilobytes, that is allowed for an individual post to the folder.

expfMessageCount.name: expfMessageCount
expfMessageCount.description: The MessageCount property indicates the number of messages in a public folder.

expfMessageWithAttachmentsCount.name: expfMessageWithAttachmentsCount
expfMessageWithAttachmentsCount.description: The MessageWithAttachmentsCount property indicates the total number of normal messages with attachments in the public folder.

expfName.name: expfName
expfName.description: The Name property indicates the name of the folder.

expfNormalMessageSize.name: expfNormalMessageSize
expfNormalMessageSize.description: The NormalMessageSize property indicates the total size, in bytes, of all of the normal messages in the public folder.

expfOwnerCount.name: expfOwnerCount
expfOwnerCount.description: The OwnerCount property indicates the number of owners of the public folder.

expfParentFriendlyUrl.name: expfParentFriendlyUrl
expfParentFriendlyUrl.description: The ParentFriendlyUrl property indicates the folder path-based URL to the parent of the folder.

expfPath.name: expfPath
expfPath.description: The Path property indicates the folder path minus the URL http://server/vroot header portion.

expfProhibitPostLimit.name: expfProhibitPostLimit
expfProhibitPostLimit.description: The ProhibitPostLimit property specifies the folder size limit, in kilobytes, when posting is prevented.

expfPublishInAddressBook.name: expfPublishInAddressBook
expfPublishInAddressBook.description: The PublishInAddressBook property specifies whether the folder will show up in the global address list if it is mail-enabled.

expfRecipientCountOnAssociateMsg.name: expfRecipientCountOnAssociateMsg
expfRecipientCountOnAssociateMsg.description: The RecipientCountOnAssociatedMessages property indicates the total number of recipients on the associated messages in the public folder.

expfRecipientCountOnNormalMsg.name: expfRecipientCountOnNormalMsg
expfRecipientCountOnNormalMsg.description: The RecipientCountOnNormalMessages property indicates the total number of recipients on the normal messages in the public folder.

expfReplicaAgeLimit.name: expfReplicaAgeLimit
expfReplicaAgeLimit.description: The ReplicaAgeLimit property specifies the age limit for messages across all replicas.

expfReplicaList.name: expfReplicaList
expfReplicaList.description: The ReplicaList property indicates the list of distinguished names of the MDBs to which the folder is replicated.

expfReplicationMessagePriority.name: expfReplicationMessagePriority
expfReplicationMessagePriority.description: The ReplicationMessagePriority property specifies the priority level for replicating folder messages.

expfReplicationSchedule.name: expfReplicationSchedule
expfReplicationSchedule.description: The array elements of the ReplicationSchedule property specify the replication schedule of the folder.

expfReplicationStyle.name: expfReplicationStyle
expfReplicationStyle.description: The ReplicationStyle property specifies how often the folder contents are replicated.

expfRestrictionCount.name: expfRestrictionCount
expfRestrictionCount.description: The RestrictionCount property indicates the total number of restrictions on the public folder.

expfSecurityDescriptor.name: expfSecurityDescriptor
expfSecurityDescriptor.description: The SecurityDescriptor property specifies the administrative security descriptor for the folder.

expfStorageLimitStyle.name: expfStorageLimitStyle
expfStorageLimitStyle.description: The StorageLimitStyle property specifies whether the folder should use public store storage limits, have no quota, or use quota values set on the folder.

expfTargetAddress.name: expfTargetAddress
expfTargetAddress.description: The TargetAddress property is a MAPI property that contains the e-mail address of the public folder.

expfTotalMessageSize.name: expfTotalMessageSize
expfTotalMessageSize.description: The TotalMessageSize property indicates the total size, in bytes, of all of the normal messages in the public folder. The TotalMessageSize property is an 8-byte version of the NormalMessageSize property.

expfUrl.name: expfUrl
expfUrl.description: The Url property indicates the folder URL, constructed using the folder globally unique identifier (GUID).

expfUsePublicStoreAgeLimits.name: expfUsePublicStoreAgeLimits
expfUsePublicStoreAgeLimits.description: The UsePublicStoreAgeLimits property specifies whether the folder should use the age limits of the MDB in which it is stored.

expfUsePublicStoreDelItemLifetm.name: expfUsePublicStoreDelItemLifetm
expfUsePublicStoreDelItemLifetm.description: The UsePublicStoreDeletedItemLifetime property specifies whether the folder should use the deleted item lifetime of the local public MDB.

expfWarningLimit.name: expfWarningLimit
expfWarningLimit.description: The WarningLimit property specifies the folder size limit, in kilobytes, when warning messages are sent.

exchangeQueueV2Table.name: exchangeQueueV2Table
exchangeQueueV2Table.description: The Exchange_Queue WMI class provides properties and methods for working with Microsoft Exchange queues.

exq2Index.name: exq2Index
exq2Index.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exq2CanEnumAll.name: exq2CanEnumAll
exq2CanEnumAll.description: The CanEnumAll property indicates whether the queue can enumerate all of the messages that it has waiting for transmission.

exq2GlobalStop.name: exq2GlobalStop
exq2GlobalStop.description: The GlobalStop property indicates whether the virtual server for the queue is in disabled mode. If True, the virtual server is disabled.

exq2LinkId.name: exq2LinkId
exq2LinkId.description: The LinkId property indicates the identifier for the link that contains the queue.

exq2LinkName.name: exq2LinkName
exq2LinkName.description: The LinkName property indicates the name of the link that contains the queue.

exq2MessageCount.name: exq2MessageCount
exq2MessageCount.description: The MessageCount property indicates the number of messages in the queue.

exq2MsgEnumFlagsSupported.name: exq2MsgEnumFlagsSupported
exq2MsgEnumFlagsSupported.description: The MsgEnumFlagsSupported property contains a mask of all enumeration flags for the queue.

exq2ProtocolName.name: exq2ProtocolName
exq2ProtocolName.description: The ProtocolName property indicates the transmission protocol for the queue.

exq2QueueId.name: exq2QueueId
exq2QueueId.description: The QueueId property indicates the identifier of the queue.

exq2QueueName.name: exq2QueueName
exq2QueueName.description: The QueueName property indicates the name of the queue.

exq2Size.name: exq2Size
exq2Size.description: The Size property indicates the message size, including attachments, in bytes.

exq2Version.name: exq2Version
exq2Version.description: The Version property indicates the version of the service that created the message tracking log entry.

exq2VirtualMachine.name: exq2VirtualMachine
exq2VirtualMachine.description: The VirtualMachine property indicates the name of the virtual machine that contains the queue.

exq2VirtualServerName.name: exq2VirtualServerName
exq2VirtualServerName.description: The VirtualServerName property indicates the name of the virtual server the queue is on.

exchangeQueueCacheReloadEvtTable.name: exchangeQueueCacheReloadEvtTable
exchangeQueueCacheReloadEvtTable.description: Instances of the Exchange_QueueCacheReloadEvent class provide information about when the queue's cache was reloaded.

exqcreIndex.name: exqcreIndex
exqcreIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exqcreReloadTime.name: exqcreReloadTime
exqcreReloadTime.description: The ReloadTime property indicates the last time that the queue provider updated its data.

exchangeQueuedMessageTable.name: exchangeQueuedMessageTable
exchangeQueuedMessageTable.description: The Exchange_QueuedMessage WMI class is the base class for the Exchange_QueuedX400Message and Exchange_QueuedSMTPMessage classes. The Exchange_QueuedMessage class provides information about messages that reside in Microsoft Exchange queues.

exqmIndex.name: exqmIndex
exqmIndex.description: The value of this object uniquely identifies the instance entry for this class.

exqmActionDeleteNDR.name: exqmActionDeleteNDR
exqmActionDeleteNDR.description: The ActionDeleteNDR property indicates whether the message supports the DeleteWithNDR method.

exqmActionDeleteNoNDR.name: exqmActionDeleteNoNDR
exqmActionDeleteNoNDR.description: The ActionDeleteNoNDR property indicates whether the message supports the DeleteWithoutNDR method.

exqmActionFreeze.name: exqmActionFreeze
exqmActionFreeze.description: The ActionFreeze property indicates whether the message supports the Freeze method.

exqmActionThaw.name: exqmActionThaw
exqmActionThaw.description: The ActionThaw property indicates whether the message supports the Thaw method.

exqmExpiry.name: exqmExpiry
exqmExpiry.description: The Expiry property indicates the expiration time stamp for the message.

exqmHighPriority.name: exqmHighPriority
exqmHighPriority.description: The HighPriority property indicates whether the message has high priority.

exqmLinkId.name: exqmLinkId
exqmLinkId.description: The LinkId property indicates the identifier for the link that contains the queued message.

exqmLinkName.name: exqmLinkName
exqmLinkName.description: The LinkName property indicates the name of the link that contains the queued message.

exqmLowPriority.name: exqmLowPriority
exqmLowPriority.description: The LowPriority property indicates whether the message has low priority.

exqmMessageId.name: exqmMessageId
exqmMessageId.description: The MessageId property indicates the identifier of the queued message.

exqmNormalPriority.name: exqmNormalPriority
exqmNormalPriority.description: The NormalPriority property indicates whether the message has normal priority.

exqmProtocolName.name: exqmProtocolName
exqmProtocolName.description: The ProtocolName property indicates the transmission protocol for the queued message.

exqmQueueId.name: exqmQueueId
exqmQueueId.description: The QueueId property indicates the identifier of the queue that the queued message is on.

exqmQueueName.name: exqmQueueName
exqmQueueName.description: The QueueName property indicates the name of the queue that contains the message.

exqmReceived.name: exqmReceived
exqmReceived.description: The Received property indicates the received time stamp for the message.

exqmRecipientCount.name: exqmRecipientCount
exqmRecipientCount.description: The RecipientCount property indicates the number of recipients in the message.

exqmRecipients.name: exqmRecipients
exqmRecipients.description: The Recipients property indicates the recipients of the message.

exqmSender.name: exqmSender
exqmSender.description: The Sender property indicates the name of the sender.

exqmSize.name: exqmSize
exqmSize.description: The Size property indicates the size of the message.

exqmStateFlags.name: exqmStateFlags
exqmStateFlags.description: The StateFlags property contains a mask of all of the state flags for the message.

exqmStateFrozen.name: exqmStateFrozen
exqmStateFrozen.description: The StateFrozen property indicates whether the message is in a frozen state.

exqmStateRetry.name: exqmStateRetry
exqmStateRetry.description: The StateRetry property indicates that transmission is being retried for a message that was not delivered successfully.

exqmSubject.name: exqmSubject
exqmSubject.description: The Subject property indicates the subject of the message.

exqmSubmission.name: exqmSubmission
exqmSubmission.description: The Submission property indicates the submission time stamp for the message.

exqmVersion.name: exqmVersion
